<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-49-0179 </DOCNO><TEXT>Irrespective of the disease causes, the clinical symptoms (hip pain, restrictedmovement) and the radiological morphology of the necroses are relativelyuniform. Several imaging methods are available for the diagnosis of hipdiseases - next to conventional radiography of the hip, the diagnosisof necroses of the femoral head may also use scintiscanning, conventionaltomography, computerized tomography, NMR tomography and, as an invasivemethod, angiography.</TEXT></DOC>